  <!-- Commute -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">Transport links</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
        How does the Wilmslow commute work?
      </h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow station handles the fastest regular commute in Cheshire: 17 minutes to Manchester Piccadilly via Avanti West Coast express services. Northern Rail runs additional stopping services averaging 28-30 minutes, giving a combined frequency of approximately 103 trains per day between 04:46 and 23:39 (National Rail, 2025).</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Three operators serve Wilmslow station: Avanti West Coast (fast services to Manchester and London Euston), Northern Rail (stopping services), and Transport for Wales. The multi-operator coverage means that service disruptions on one line rarely eliminate all connections.</p>

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin: 24px 0;">
        {[
          { dest: 'Manchester Piccadilly', time: '17 min', note: 'Avanti express' },
          { dest: 'Manchester Airport', time: '7 min', note: 'Northern Rail direct' },
          { dest: 'London Euston', time: '2 hr 5 min', note: 'Avanti West Coast' },
          { dest: 'Stockport', time: '8 min', note: 'Northern Rail' },
        ].map((route) => (
          <div style="background-color: #F9F7F4; border: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: 20px;">
