            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">{route.dest}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">{route.note}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Manchester Airport proximity</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow sits four miles from Manchester Airport - a 7-minute direct train or 9-minute drive. This proximity makes the town a practical base for frequent business travellers and households with international connections. No other Cheshire town of comparable size and quality offers this level of airport access.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Wilmslow road and motorway connections</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Wilmslow connects to the M60 orbital motorway and Manchester city centre via the A34. Off-peak, the drive to Manchester takes approximately 30 minutes. Peak-hour congestion on the A34 and Wilmslow Road corridor adds 15-25 minutes, making the train materially faster for daily commuters. <em style="color: #888888; font-size: 14px;">(Sources: National Rail, 2025; Google Maps typical travel times)</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Schools -->
