      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow High School serves as the main secondary for the entire Golden Triangle area, drawing pupils from Alderley Edge and Prestbury as well as Wilmslow itself. Its Progress 8 score of +0.16 means pupils make slightly above-average progress compared to similar students nationally (DfE, 2024). The 58% grade 5+ in English and Maths exceeds the national average of 30.84%.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Gorsey Bank Primary and Ashdene Primary are the two Outstanding-rated state primaries. Gorsey Bank, in particular, received exemplary ratings across all inspection categories in 2023. School catchment boundaries directly influence property prices - streets within the Gorsey Bank or Ashdene catchments command measurable premiums over otherwise comparable properties outside the boundary. Families weighing school options alongside budget should read the <a href="/buying-guide/making-offer-cheshire" style="color: #3D5A3E;">guide to making an offer in Cheshire</a>.</p>
