  <!-- Lifestyle -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">Wilmslow amenity and services</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
        What is daily life like in Wilmslow?
      </h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow's daily life centres on Bank Square and pedestrianised Grove Street, with Hoopers department store, Waitrose, Sainsbury's, and over 100 independent boutiques within walking distance of the station - a retail offer unavailable in any other Cheshire Golden Triangle town.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Wilmslow dining and restaurants</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow's restaurant scene spans Italian (Cibo, Piccolino), Neapolitan pizza (Wood Fire Smoke on Water Lane), Indian (Potyo - 4.9 rating), and American smokehouse (Hickory's on Racecourse Road). For evening drinks, The Ladybrook pub and Coach and Four provide traditional alternatives to the wine bar scene. The dining offer is broader and more diverse than neighbouring Alderley Edge, which concentrates on premium-only venues.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Wilmslow parks and outdoors</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow's flagship park, The Carrs, runs 71 acres along the River Bollin, a 10-minute walk from the town centre. The park hosts Wilmslow's weekly Parkrun (Saturday 9am), a children's play area, and riverside walking trails connecting to Quarry Bank Mill - a National Trust property with 400 acres of woodland and a preserved 18th-century cotton mill built by Samuel Greg. On the western side of town, Lindow Common (SSSI) provides lowland heath walking through protected birch woodland.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Wilmslow Artisan Market and events</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">The Wilmslow Artisan Market runs on the third Saturday of each month (except January) on Alderley Road and South Drive, with over 120 traders, street food stalls, and live entertainment. The market has won national awards since launching in 2011 and draws visitors from across east Cheshire. Wilmslow Live, a free summer music event on Bank Square, and the annual Running Festival (half marathon, 10K, and fun run) round out the community calendar.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Safety -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">Crime and security data</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
        Is Wilmslow safe?
      </h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Yes. Wilmslow records a crime rate of 51.4 per 1,000 population (police.uk, 2025), which is 44% below the national average of 91.6 per 1,000 and 12% below the Cheshire average of 58 per 1,000 (Cheshire Constabulary, 2024/25). The year-on-year trend shows a 2.1% decline in recorded crime.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">The most commonly reported categories are anti-social behaviour and low-level theft, consistent with a town centre that draws evening and weekend visitors. Violent crime and burglary rates sit below Cheshire East averages. The Cheshire Constabulary neighbourhood policing team covers Wilmslow, Handforth, and Alderley Edge from the Wilmslow Police Station on Swan Street.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- History and Heritage -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">Wilmslow origins and notable residents</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
        What is Wilmslow's history?
      </h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Wilmslow derives its name from Old English "Wighelmes hlaw" - the mound of a man called Wighelm. Before the railway arrived in 1842, the parish comprised a few farms, a church, and a population of 2,842 (Census, 1801). The Manchester to Crewe railway transformed the settlement, drawing wealthy merchants who built the Victorian and Georgian houses that still define the town's residential character.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Two heritage facts distinguish Wilmslow from neighbouring towns. Alan Turing - mathematician, Enigma codebreaker, and pioneer of computer science - lived at 43 Adlington Road until his death in 1954. A blue plaque marks the house, and Turing Drive is named in his honour. Separately, the Lindow Man, an Iron Age bog body preserved in peat for over 2,000 years, was discovered in Lindow Moss on the town's western edge in the 1980s and is now exhibited in the British Museum.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Post-war suburban development consolidated Wilmslow's role as Manchester's primary commuter settlement. The town's contemporary reputation - luxury retail, footballer residents, the Real Housewives of Cheshire filming locations - reflects its evolution from agricultural parish to one of the most affluent communities in northern England.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

